OL,3,CConcerns over costs to deliver
OL,4,CJersey's new hospital, report finds
OL,6,FIndependent UK advisers were recruited
OL,7,Fto assess the programme's business
OL,8,Fcase and have facilitated the building
OL,9,Fof several NHS hospitals.
OL,11,FThey have reported that the
OL,12,Fgovernment's plans are "not
OL,13,Fsufficiently developed for a scheme of
OL,14,Fthis scale and significance".
OL,16,FThis is despite Jersey's Planning
OL,17,FCommittee unanimously signing off on
OL,18,Fplans for the #710 million acute
OL,19,Fhospital at Overdale.
